cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper presents a new hardware architecture for in-memory computing, which is the main focus of the paper.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed architecture for deep neural networks, which is a common application of in-memory computing.
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper describes the integration of the in-memory computing accelerator with an embedded CPU, which is a key aspect of the proposed architecture.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the spatial architecture of in-memory computing, which is a form of distributed computing.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a new system architecture for in-memory computing, which involves control of the processing elements and dataflow.
